article.headline: East Tenn. St. 81, Stetson 72
article.story: DELAND, Fla. (AP) -- Senior point guard Tim Smith scored 13 of his team-high 21 points in the second half to lead East Tennessee State to an 81-72 victory over Stetson Thursday. Senior forward Dillion Sneed added 14 points and nine rebounds, while junior guard Travis Strong chipped in 13 points and senior guard Ben Rhoda contributed 12 points for ETSU. Stetson was led by senior guard E.J. Gordon, who scored a season-high 26 points and grabbed 10 rebounds. Freshman guard Kris Thomas added 10 points for the Hatters. ETSU won for the eighth time in its last eight games, improving to 9-7 overall and 6-3 in the Atlantic Sun Conference. Stetson dropped its fourth consecutive game and fell to 2-14 overall and 2-6 in conference. The Hatters held a 14-11 lead 7:20 into the game, but after Stetson substituted for all five starters the Buccaneers went on a 9-0 run for a 20-14 lead. ETSU continued its rally, extending the run to a 16-2 advantage, to build a 27-16 lead with 8:01 left in the first half. Sneed led the way with six of his 10 first-half points. The Hatters got within five points, 75-70 with 1:01 left on Will Holloman's layup, but ETSU made six of eight free throws to protect its lead in the final minute.
